Privacy Policy
We provide services, apps, and games that collect data from you and your children, and we have a Privacy Policy document to govern this. This Privacy Policy outlines how we handle the personal information you provide or that we collect while providing services to you. It complies with the United States Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and the European General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
User Consent:
By installing our apps on your mobile device, accessing, or using them, you agree to the terms and conditions laid out in this Privacy Policy, including the possible collection and processing of your personal data. You acknowledge that your personal data may be collected, and you cannot use our services if you do not agree.
Note:
If you, or your legal guardian, disagree with any term provided herein, please refrain from installing, accessing, or using our apps and promptly delete all our apps from your mobile device.
Purpose of This Privacy Policy:
We prioritize the protection of your personal data, and this Privacy Policy aims to clearly and comprehensively explain what information we collect, how we use, monitor, and share it.
Changes to the Privacy Policy:
We may update the terms of this Privacy Policy periodically, so please check back frequently to understand how we use your personal data. In the event of a significant change, we will provide notice on our website. If we have your parent's email address, we will notify them of the changes.
Data Collection:
What information do we collect about our users?
Non-personal Information:
We use third-party providers to collect non-personal and non-identifiable information (e.g., technical and behavioral data).
Contact Information:
When you contact us, you may provide your contact details such as phone number and email.
Technical Data:
We collect information like IP address, device identifiers, and other technical data from devices used to access our services.
Usage Data:
We gather information on how our services and games are used or played, which does not identify you personally but helps us improve and customize our offerings.
Disclosure of Personal Data:
We may share your personal data with:
Group companies, third-party service providers, and data processing partners to deliver our services.
Law enforcement or regulatory authorities where disclosure is required by law or to protect our rights.
Third-Party Services:
You may use third-party services in conjunction with our apps, subject to their own terms and privacy policies. We are not responsible for how these third parties use your data.
External Links:
Our games may contain ads and links to external websites. We are not liable for the security of information you provide on these sites.
Privacy Policy for Apps Global Studio:
We may request the following information with user consent:
Name, contact details including email address
Demographic information and preferences for surveys or offers
Advertising:
We carefully select third-party advertisers whose ads may appear in our apps. Clicking on these ads may allow advertisers to collect data through cookies and similar technologies.
Changes to the Privacy Policy:
We reserve the right to change this policy at any time. Please revisit this page periodically for updates. For any inquiries, contact us at "
muhammadjunaidashraf661@gmail.com
". This version aims to be clearer and more structured, focusing on key privacy concerns and user rights.
